cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL

The paper discusses a faster algorithm for CTL (Computation Tree Logic) which is a temporal logic used in formal verification of software systems. This makes it likely to be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these sub-categories deal with formal methods and reasoning. It could also be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it discusses software verification. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) as it deals with temporal logics and automata theory.
